<item>
            <title>[SPARK-11998] Branch 1.6&apos;s hadoop 2.2 tests always fail the entire VersionsSuite</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-11998</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Right now, we hardcoded hadoop 2.4 to download when we need to download hive and hadoop jars for metadata hive. However, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-9596&quot; title=&quot;Avoid reloading Hadoop classes like UserGroupInformation&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPARK-9596&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPARK-9596&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; makes isoalted client loader share hadoop classes. So, if there is any compatibility issues between the shared hadoop and hadoop 2.4, VersionsSuite will failed. Actually, in spark 1.6&apos;s hadoop 2.2 tests, VersionsSuite always fail (&lt;a href=&quot;https://amplab.cs.berkeley.edu/jenkins/view/Spark%20QA%20Dashboard%20(Patrick)/job/Spark-1.6-SBT/AMPLAB_JENKINS_BUILD_PROFILE=hadoop2.2,label=spark-test/40/testReport/junit/org.apache.spark.sql.hive.client/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://amplab.cs.berkeley.edu/jenkins/view/Spark%20QA%20Dashboard%20(Patrick)/job/Spark-1.6-SBT/AMPLAB_JENKINS_BUILD_PROFILE=hadoop2.2,label=spark-test/40/testReport/junit/org.apache.spark.sql.hive.client/&lt;/a&gt;). Because &lt;tt&gt;HftpFileSystem&lt;/tt&gt; has been moved to a new location in Hadoop 2.3+. From Hadoop 2.4, we get &lt;tt&gt;org.apache.hadoop.hdfs.web.HftpFileSystem&lt;/tt&gt;. But, when we look up the class (by looking at hadoop 2.2&apos;s jars), it is not in this location.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
